\begin_layout Subsection*
Proof of correspondence with Gwet (2021)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using the nominal disagreement function, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Gwet2021-ht"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 uses the following estimator for the asymptotic variance of the pairwise
 Fleiss' kappa:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{\sigma}^{2}=\frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(\kappa_{i}^{\star}-\hat{\kappa})^{2}.
\]

\end_inset

Translating into our notation (dropping the dependence on the disagreement
 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

), we have that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\kappa}=1-\hat{D}/\hat{F}$
\end_inset

.
 Moreover, one can verify that 
\begin_inset Formula $\kappa_{i}^{\star}$
\end_inset

 equals
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\kappa_{i}^{\star}=1-\frac{\hat{\mu}(x_{i})}{\hat{F}}-2\frac{\hat{D}}{\hat{F}}\left(1-\frac{\hat{\mu}_{f}(x_{i})}{\hat{F}}\right).
\]

\end_inset

Following a small reorganization of the terms, we find that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(\kappa_{i}^{\star}-\hat{\kappa})^{2}=\frac{1}{\hat{F}^{2}}\frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\left(2\frac{\hat{D}}{\hat{F}}\left[\hat{\mu}_{f}(x_{i})-\hat{F}\right]-[\hat{\mu}_{d}(x_{i})-\hat{D}]\right)^{2}.
\]

\end_inset

Using the definitions of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\sigma}_{D}^{2},\hat{\sigma}_{FD}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\sigma}_{F}^{2}$
\end_inset

 (section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Estimating-the-variances"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

), one can easily verify that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\left(\kappa_{i}^{\star}-\hat{\kappa}\right)^{2} & = & \frac{1}{\hat{F}^{2}}\left(\hat{\sigma}_{D}^{2}-2\hat{\sigma}_{FD}\frac{\hat{D}_{d}}{\hat{F}_{d}}+\hat{\sigma}_{F}^{2}\frac{\hat{D}_{d}^{2}}{\hat{F}_{d}^{2}}\right),
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

hence the estimator of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Gwet2021-ht"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 is a special case of the proposed estimator in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Estimating-the-variances"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
